# Marine Intelligence Data Normalization

This notebook demonstrates the normalization process for
marine intelligence datasets including AIS vessel signals,
weather observations, and hydrology measurements.

The goal is to standardize heterogeneous datasets into a
unified schema before ingestion into the Marine Intelligence
Signal Database.

#Import Libraries
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

#Load Raw Datasets
ais = pd.read_csv("../data/ais_standardized.csv")
weather = pd.read_csv("../data/weather_standardized.csv")
water = pd.read_csv("../data/water_standardized.csv")

ais.head()

#Select Standard Schema
columns = [
    "source_id",
    "timestamp",
    "latitude",
    "longitude",
    "feature_type",
    "normalized_value",
    "source_reference"
]

ais = ais[columns]
weather = weather[columns]
water = water[columns]

#Merge Datasets
final_data = pd.concat(
    [ais, weather, water],
    ignore_index=True
)

final_data.head()

#Timestamp Standardization
final_data["timestamp"] = pd.to_datetime(
    final_data["timestamp"],
    errors="coerce"
)

#Data Validation
valid_df = final_data[
    (final_data["latitude"].between(-90,90)) &
    (final_data["longitude"].between(-180,180)) &
    (final_data["normalized_value"].notnull())
]

valid_df.head()

#Visualization
valid_df["feature_type"].value_counts().plot(kind="bar")
plt.title("Distribution of Signal Types")
plt.show()

#Final Dataset Ready for Ingestion
print("Total records:", len(final_data))
print("Valid records:", len(valid_df))
print("Rejected records:", len(final_data) - len(valid_df))

#Signal Inventory Concept
Signal Inventory Query:

SELECT feature_type, COUNT(*)
FROM marine_signals
GROUP BY feature_type;

This query summarizes the number of signals of each type
stored in the Marine Intelligence Signal Database.
